byline.original: By MICHAEL D. SHEAR and JEFF ZELENY

snippet: South Carolina’s decision to schedule its Republican primary for Jan. 21 adds pressure on Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey to make a decision about running for president.
lead_paragraph: South Carolina’s decision to schedule its Republican primary for Jan. 21 adds pressure on Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey to make a decision about running for president.
